1:07:03.184 --> 1:07:05.687
No, really, really,
and lucky too.

1:07:13.528 --> 1:07:15.197
Where's Harry?

1:07:15.229 --> 1:07:16.998
His son took him.

1:07:22.604 --> 1:07:23.638
Have you ever played
slots with him?

1:07:23.671 --> 1:07:24.573
No.

1:07:24.606 --> 1:07:26.640
Oh you should, you should.

1:07:26.673 --> 1:07:27.575
What?

1:07:27.608 --> 1:07:28.610
We nearly hit the big one.

1:07:28.642 --> 1:07:29.644
Really, that's fantastic.

1:07:29.677 --> 1:07:30.711
You know the big one?

1:07:30.744 --> 1:07:32.046
No, no, I don't know what
you're talking about.

1:07:32.079 --> 1:07:33.481
Oh, right, right, right here!

1:07:33.514 --> 1:07:36.050
This is a big one
that pays $10,000.

1:07:36.084 --> 1:07:37.185
Wow $10,000, that's fantastic.

1:07:37.218 --> 1:07:39.588
Yeah, yeah, you want
to give it a try?

1:07:39.621 --> 1:07:41.088
No, I don't want to...

1:07:41.122 --> 1:07:43.158
No no no, you should try, maybe
you're lucky like your father.

1:07:43.191 --> 1:07:44.126
Oh yeah?

1:07:44.159 --> 1:07:45.626
I don't want to play
the slot machine, okay.

1:07:45.660 --> 1:07:47.496
Now what the hell
is taking so long?

1:07:47.528 --> 1:07:50.164
Let him sit in peace.

1:07:50.197 --> 1:07:52.500
You know, if it's a
number two he's doing,

1:07:52.534 --> 1:07:55.169
that can take a while,
especially at our age.

1:08:03.644 --> 1:08:05.112
Psst.

1:08:05.146 --> 1:08:07.215
Harry, what are you doing?

1:08:07.247 --> 1:08:09.851
No time to explain.

1:08:11.151 --> 1:08:14.155
This is your last chance, kid.

1:08:14.188 --> 1:08:15.724
For what?

1:08:15.756 --> 1:08:19.294
To give a dying
man his final wish.

1:08:19.326 --> 1:08:21.295
Take me to Olompali.

1:08:21.329 --> 1:08:22.863
What about your son?

1:08:22.897 --> 1:08:24.099
Chucky?

1:08:24.131 --> 1:08:26.735
I gave him the slip,
but not for long.

1:08:26.768 --> 1:08:28.303
Harry, if I were to do this,

1:08:28.335 --> 1:08:30.204
I would get in so much trouble.

1:08:30.237 --> 1:08:32.139
He would probably
have me arrested

1:08:32.173 --> 1:08:33.808
for, I don't know, kidnapping.

1:08:33.840 --> 1:08:36.777
Kidnapping? I'm a free man

1:08:36.811 --> 1:08:39.281
going on an outing
with a friend!

1:08:39.313 --> 1:08:41.015
That's not a crime.

1:08:41.049 --> 1:08:44.619
What about my job,
if I still have one?

1:08:44.652 --> 1:08:49.124
Oh right, would hate for
you to give up all that.

1:08:49.156 --> 1:08:52.693
Relax, I'll take the
fall, what do you say?

1:08:57.264 --> 1:09:00.102
All right, forget it

1:09:02.236 --> 1:09:03.271
Harry.

1:09:03.304 --> 1:09:04.540
What?

1:09:06.240 --> 1:09:09.744
Can't make a gain unless
you take a risk, right?

1:09:09.777 --> 1:09:10.946
That's right.

1:09:10.978 --> 1:09:13.113
Well, come on then.

1:09:13.147 --> 1:09:14.182
What?

1:09:14.214 --> 1:09:16.584
We're going to Olompali.

1:09:16.617 --> 1:09:18.753
Now you're talking.

1:09:20.021 --> 1:09:21.990
Let's get out of
these silly outfits.

1:09:22.022 --> 1:09:23.223
You said it.

1:09:23.256 --> 1:09:24.925
I come from Long
Island, ever been?

1:09:24.959 --> 1:09:26.126
Yeah, East Hampton.

1:09:26.160 --> 1:09:28.129
Oh, East Hampton, that's lovely.

1:09:28.161 --> 1:09:31.231
But you know, Long Island,
it's all right I guess, but oh,

1:09:31.264 --> 1:09:33.668
those winters,
they will kill you.

1:09:33.701 --> 1:09:36.338
At my age, there aren't
enough layers, you know?

1:09:36.370 --> 1:09:37.905
Just please stop talking.

1:09:37.938 --> 1:09:39.640
Okay, this is
taking way too long.

1:09:43.811 --> 1:09:44.646
Shit!

1:09:51.251 --> 1:09:52.253
Red!

1:09:52.286 --> 1:09:54.690
They took Harry!

1:09:58.860 --> 1:10:01.662
Oh, Mr.
Butler, I am so sorry.

1:10:01.696 --> 1:10:03.298
I gave
your car away.

1:10:03.330 --> 1:10:05.633
What, you gave it away?

1:10:05.666 --> 1:10:08.202
Yes, I held it for quite a
while, but when you didn't come

1:10:08.236 --> 1:10:10.338
I had to give it
to someone else.

1:10:10.370 --> 1:10:12.906
But no worries, Mr.
Byrd's son is here.

1:10:12.939 --> 1:10:14.909
I'm sure he'll give you a ride.

1:10:14.942 --> 1:10:17.613
Yes, yes, I am sure he will.

1:10:18.045 --> 1:10:19.046
Thank you.

1:10:20.947 --> 1:10:21.348
Secret plan.

1:10:21.381 --> 1:10:22.282
What's that?

1:10:22.317 --> 1:10:23.918
I'll let you know when
I come up with it.

1:10:23.951 --> 1:10:25.286
Jay, Harry, what's going on?

1:10:25.318 --> 1:10:27.354
Red, we have got to get out of
here, but we don't have a vehicle.

1:10:27.388 --> 1:10:29.024
Okay well calm
down, I'll take you.

1:10:29.057 --> 1:10:30.025
Where are you guys going?

1:10:30.058 --> 1:10:31.026
Olompali.

1:10:31.058 --> 1:10:32.192
Olompali?

1:10:32.226 --> 1:10:33.695
I stalled him as
long as I could,

1:10:33.728 --> 1:10:35.731
but he's looking for you now.

1:10:36.930 --> 1:10:37.965
Okay, you know what, let's go.

1:10:37.999 --> 1:10:39.300
Come with me.

1:10:54.048 --> 1:10:55.349
A nice house, is it yours?

1:10:55.383 --> 1:10:57.318
Yes it is, come on in.

1:10:57.351 --> 1:10:58.318
What about the other girls?

1:10:58.352 --> 1:10:59.787
Don't worry about them,
they know what to do.

1:10:59.821 --> 1:11:00.988
I'll pick them up tomorrow.

1:11:10.164 --> 1:11:11.299
Hey!

1:11:11.331 --> 1:11:12.366
Stop it!

1:11:14.802 --> 1:11:17.972
What are you doing, no! Come on!

1:11:18.004 --> 1:11:20.141
You've got to be kidding me!

1:11:21.808 --> 1:11:23.043
What the hell is this?

1:11:23.076 --> 1:11:24.311
Hey mister, can you
give us a jumpstart?

1:11:24.344 --> 1:11:25.813
- What?
- I think our battery's dead.

1:11:25.847 --> 1:11:26.648
No.

1:11:26.680 --> 1:11:28.049
We're really stuck,
give us a hand.

1:11:28.081 --> 1:11:29.349
I'm sorry, I can't help you.

1:11:29.383 --> 1:11:31.251
Say, aren't you Harry's son?

1:11:31.285 --> 1:11:32.287
What?

1:11:32.320 --> 1:11:33.287
Harry's son?

1:11:33.321 --> 1:11:34.322
I really love Harry.

1:11:34.354 --> 1:11:35.990
- Can I give you a hug?
- No!

1:11:36.022 --> 1:11:38.159
Look, I have to go, I have to,
just please don't touch me!

1:11:38.192 --> 1:11:40.361
Hey buddy, that's
not very neighborly.

1:11:40.393 --> 1:11:43.698
Now you need to apologize
to the nice ladies.

1:11:45.832 --> 1:11:46.434
Shit.

1:11:48.302 --> 1:11:51.272
Okay, okay.

1:12:04.018 --> 1:12:05.220
They're asleep.

1:12:05.253 --> 1:12:07.389
Look how sweet that is.

1:12:08.856 --> 1:12:10.525
You know, you too
can go to sleep.

1:12:10.558 --> 1:12:12.160
I got this handled.

1:12:12.192 --> 1:12:14.762
Oh, no thanks, I'm
still too wired.

1:12:18.198 --> 1:12:20.535
So what's the deal
with you and this guy?

1:12:20.567 --> 1:12:22.236
I mean, you said he
wasn't your father.

1:12:22.269 --> 1:12:25.906
No, no, no, my father
passed away recently.

1:12:25.939 --> 1:12:26.840
Oh, I'm so sorry.

1:12:26.874 --> 1:12:29.043
Oh don't be, what I mean to say

1:12:29.076 --> 1:12:31.212
is we weren't that close.

1:12:31.245 --> 1:12:33.348
You know that happens.

1:12:33.380 --> 1:12:37.451
Yeah, anyway I'm taking
Harry to his new home,

1:12:37.485 --> 1:12:39.019
the one he doesn't
want to go to.

1:12:39.053 --> 1:12:41.156
Yeah that must be kind of hard.

1:12:41.188 --> 1:12:44.793
He's just desperate to get
to this place Olompali.

1:12:44.826 --> 1:12:46.227
Why?

1:12:46.259 --> 1:12:47.961
I'm not exactly sure.

1:12:47.995 --> 1:12:51.131
Good times, a last
flame, I don't know.

1:12:51.165 --> 1:12:56.171
Well it is very beautiful, I
haven't been there in years.

1:12:56.204 --> 1:12:57.371
Never been.

1:12:57.405 --> 1:13:00.441
So what do you do when you...

1:13:00.473 --> 1:13:01.275
In real life?

1:13:03.344 --> 1:13:05.847
Well, I'm an accountant, honey.

1:13:05.879 --> 1:13:06.480
You're kidding.

1:13:06.513 --> 1:13:08.048
For real.

1:13:08.081 --> 1:13:11.186
What you thinking,
wild burlesque dancer

1:13:11.219 --> 1:13:13.421
can't hold down a
straight day job?

1:13:13.454 --> 1:13:15.055
I didn't think a
straight day job holder

1:13:15.089 --> 1:13:17.959
could be a wild crazy
burlesque dancer.

1:13:18.625 --> 1:13:20.327
It's a wild world, baby!

1:13:20.361 --> 1:13:21.863
I guess it is.

1:13:26.233 --> 1:13:29.504
You know, I really
want to thank you.

1:13:29.536 --> 1:13:31.271
You saved our ass back there.

1:13:31.304 --> 1:13:34.174
Oh, Red, that's
sweet, but no problem.

1:13:34.207 --> 1:13:38.280
Actually, I have to
say, you saved mine.

1:14:34.335 --> 1:14:39.341
Wow, whoa, this-this
is really something!

1:14:40.473 --> 1:14:41.508
Harry!

1:14:41.541 --> 1:14:43.678
What'd I tell you?

1:14:43.710 --> 1:14:46.046
Harry, are you okay?

1:14:46.080 --> 1:14:47.314
Never better.

1:14:47.348 --> 1:14:49.384
Hey, where are you going?

1:14:49.416 --> 1:14:52.987
Hey, he's off, I've got
to keep an eye on him.

1:14:53.687 --> 1:14:55.088
Have you been here?

1:14:55.121 --> 1:14:58.125
Yeah, long time
ago. So beautiful.

1:15:11.405 --> 1:15:13.340
Hey, Harry!

1:15:16.076 --> 1:15:19.046
Harry, hey, hey, hey!

1:15:19.080 --> 1:15:21.448
What's the damn
hurry there, partner?

1:15:21.482 --> 1:15:22.384
The Outlook.

1:15:23.483 --> 1:15:25.320
What's next, Everest?

1:15:25.353 --> 1:15:26.654
Come on.

1:15:26.687 --> 1:15:28.356
Oh, for God's sake,
Harry, slow down.

1:15:40.300 --> 1:15:43.303
Harriet and I used to
hike down to that beach.

1:15:43.336 --> 1:15:45.307
What are you, part
mountain goat?

1:15:47.441 --> 1:15:48.309
That's nothing.

1:15:49.244 --> 1:15:52.313
We hung out with the
seals and sea lions.

1:15:52.345 --> 1:15:56.049
Saw a dolphin, even
some whales up there.

1:15:56.082 --> 1:15:57.617
Harry, that's good times.

1:15:57.651 --> 1:15:58.586
The best.

1:16:06.527 --> 1:16:07.996
Harry?
Yeah?

1:16:09.429 --> 1:16:12.066
You remember when you said
your father was an SOB?

1:16:13.666 --> 1:16:14.568
Yeah.

1:16:14.602 --> 1:16:18.272
My father, he was an SOB too.

1:16:18.304 --> 1:16:19.272
I know that.

1:16:19.305 --> 1:16:21.075
You do?

1:16:21.107 --> 1:16:23.244
Yeah, I can tell
by the way you are.

1:16:24.378 --> 1:16:26.680
You remind me of myself
when I was your age.

1:16:26.714 --> 1:16:27.648
How's that?

1:16:27.680 --> 1:16:31.052
Beaten down, unsure of things.

1:16:31.085 --> 1:16:32.687
But bursting with life.

1:16:34.054 --> 1:16:36.523
You see those trips
here with Harriet,

1:16:36.557 --> 1:16:38.226
that's what kept me going.

1:16:39.192 --> 1:16:41.262
Just like acting
keeps you going.

1:16:42.830 --> 1:16:45.166
If I were you, I'd be
pissed at my old man.

1:16:45.198 --> 1:16:47.535
You have a right to be,
he wasn't there for you.

1:16:47.567 --> 1:16:49.102
And I'll tell you
something else.

1:16:49.135 --> 1:16:51.539
Only by getting pissed
can you forgive him.

1:16:52.540 --> 1:16:54.242
I don't understand.

1:16:54.275 --> 1:16:55.677
What was your father's name?

1:16:57.143 --> 1:16:58.545
Grit.

1:16:58.579 --> 1:17:01.715
We all have a good and bad side.

1:17:01.749 --> 1:17:04.419
Me, you, even Grit.

1:17:06.086 --> 1:17:09.389
We get to choose, Grit just
didn't know he could choose.

1:17:09.423 --> 1:17:12.227
That was tough on you,
but worse for him.

1:17:14.862 --> 1:17:16.264
I guess so.

1:17:16.296 --> 1:17:17.398
I know so.

1:17:18.365 --> 1:17:20.501
Anyway, you still have time.

1:17:20.534 --> 1:17:21.736
For what?

1:17:21.768 --> 1:17:24.671
To be proud of who you
are and what you do.

1:17:25.872 --> 1:17:29.343
No matter what the
result, just live.

1:17:29.375 --> 1:17:33.814
Okay, okay, thanks Harry,
thanks, thanks a lot.

1:17:35.381 --> 1:17:40.120
Ah, today's a good day to die.

1:17:41.287 --> 1:17:42.424
Just kidding.

1:17:45.159 --> 1:17:47.195
I came into this world crying

1:17:47.228 --> 1:17:49.330
and I'll go out laughing.

1:17:49.362 --> 1:17:51.365
Look, right
there, there they are.

1:17:51.397 --> 1:17:54.302
Uh-oh, party's over.

1:18:01.142 --> 1:18:02.876
That's him officer, that's
the guy right there.

1:18:02.910 --> 1:18:03.577
Come on, Dad.

1:18:03.611 --> 1:18:04.612
What seems to be the problem?

1:18:04.644 --> 1:18:05.812
Are you kidding me?

1:18:05.845 --> 1:18:07.482
You kidnapped my father, I'm
filing charges against you.

1:18:07.514 --> 1:18:09.383
I wasn't kidnapped.

1:18:09.415 --> 1:18:11.218
That's right officer,
Harry wanted to come here.

1:18:11.251 --> 1:18:12.786
You tell him, girl.

1:18:12.820 --> 1:18:14.354
Okay, but if you
file a complaint

1:18:14.388 --> 1:18:15.590
I'll have to write a report.

1:18:15.622 --> 1:18:20.527
Let him go or I'm not moving.

1:18:20.561 --> 1:18:21.461
Now, Dad.

1:18:21.495 --> 1:18:24.564
Don't now Dad me, Charles.

1:18:24.598 --> 1:18:26.234
I know deep down you mean well,

1:18:26.267 --> 1:18:28.436
but no harm was done.

1:18:28.469 --> 1:18:32.439
In fact, I had the
time of my life.

1:18:39.812 --> 1:18:42.182
All right. Okay fine,
forget about it.

1:18:42.215 --> 1:18:43.517
Please, Dad.

1:18:55.396 --> 1:18:57.331
You stay away from my father.

1:19:00.934 --> 1:19:03.271
Bye, Harry.

1:19:03.304 --> 1:19:07.642
So long Jay. You take care.

1:19:09.777 --> 1:19:10.612
I will.

1:20:18.778 --> 1:20:21.415
Damn. Damn.

1:20:22.415 --> 1:20:24.384
I guess it was worse
for you than anyone.

1:20:26.053 --> 1:20:28.488
I know now, I know.

1:20:40.601 --> 1:20:41.568
Goodbye, Dad.

1:20:45.438 --> 1:20:46.340
I love you.

1:20:59.018 --> 1:21:01.421
I heard Harry
got used to the Golden Oaks.

1:21:01.455 --> 1:21:02.923
He even liked it.

1:21:02.955 --> 1:21:05.726
When the time came,
his passing was easy.

1:21:28.348 --> 1:21:30.418
A few weeks after Harry died,

1:21:30.451 --> 1:21:34.421
I got a call from his lawyer,
George, same as my father's.

1:21:34.455 --> 1:21:36.424
He wouldn't tell me
what it was about.

1:21:36.456 --> 1:21:38.425
He said we had to meet.

1:21:42.763 --> 1:21:45.433
Jay, nice to see you,
thank you for coming.

1:21:45.465 --> 1:21:46.300
Have a seat.

1:21:50.137 --> 1:21:53.073
I know this is a bit awkward
so I'll get right to it.

1:21:54.540 --> 1:21:57.677
Some time ago, I received
a recording from Harry.

1:21:57.710 --> 1:22:00.548
He wanted me to play it for
you all after he was gone.

1:22:01.749 --> 1:22:05.620
So. Here it is.

1:22:09.455 --> 1:22:13.627
Hello. I hope this
damn thing works.

1:22:16.162 --> 1:22:18.398
Well, I bet you
thought you'd seen

1:22:18.432 --> 1:22:21.836
the last of me, guess again.

1:22:21.869 --> 1:22:23.470
You don't get off that easy.

1:22:24.437 --> 1:22:27.741
By the time you see
this, I'll be long gone,

1:22:27.775 --> 1:22:29.376
but that's okay.

1:22:29.410 --> 1:22:31.813
Don't cry for me, Argentina,
I'm in a better place.

1:22:33.479 --> 1:22:37.485
Anyways, you kids know I've
divided my considerable estate

1:22:37.518 --> 1:22:42.423
between the three of you. Manage
it wisely and for God sake,

1:22:42.455 --> 1:22:44.458
have some fun with the money.

1:22:46.125 --> 1:22:48.829
I know maybe I wasn't
the best of fathers.

1:22:48.862 --> 1:22:52.166
You are but I was a damn
sight better than my old man

1:22:52.198 --> 1:22:54.468
and did my best.

1:22:54.500 --> 1:22:57.604
Know that I loved you,
and no hard feelings

1:22:57.638 --> 1:23:01.042
about sending me off to the
old folks home at the end.

1:23:02.675 --> 1:23:05.412
Now I wanted my
friend Jay to be here

1:23:05.446 --> 1:23:09.049
because there's one property
I wanted him to have,

1:23:09.081 --> 1:23:10.985
the old Magnolia Theater.

1:23:11.018 --> 1:23:12.953
Don't get excited,
it ain't much,

1:23:12.986 --> 1:23:15.089
you kids won't miss it a bit.

1:23:16.557 --> 1:23:19.193
I just saw Jay might enjoy
it and put it to good use,

1:23:19.226 --> 1:23:22.662
maybe put on a comedy show
now and then, who knows.

1:23:23.830 --> 1:23:27.867
Okay, well
that's about it.

1:23:27.901 --> 1:23:31.505
Take care and see you around.

1:23:33.573 --> 1:23:34.776
Dad really liked you.

1:23:46.186 --> 1:23:49.490
Okay, watch your
step folks, please.

1:23:49.522 --> 1:23:53.126
And if you want to remember
me in your wills, Jay Butler.

1:23:54.193 --> 1:23:56.162
You're so funny.

1:23:56.196 --> 1:23:58.198
What, you think I'm joking?

1:24:00.500 --> 1:24:03.204
I kept my job and
started doing acting on the side.

1:24:05.539 --> 1:24:06.907
I even got the kids involved.

1:24:06.939 --> 1:24:08.875
Since the property
was free and clear,

1:24:08.909 --> 1:24:10.777
I was able to borrow against it.

1:24:10.811 --> 1:24:13.714
That and a settlement I
got from my father's estate

1:24:13.746 --> 1:24:16.683
was more than enough for Danny's
college fund, Chloe's too.

1:24:19.286 --> 1:24:21.489
Danny surprised
the hell out of me

1:24:21.522 --> 1:24:24.492
when he told me he
wanted to study acting.

1:24:37.271 --> 1:24:39.639
Even Susan and I made our peace.

1:24:49.316 --> 1:24:52.086
So that pretty much
brings you up to date.

1:24:52.119 --> 1:24:54.889
Now you may not think my
life story is exactly comedy,

1:24:54.921 --> 1:24:59.927
but let me tell you, it's
